Findings: Single portable view of the chest. Low lung volumes are again noted. Chronic changes compatible with patients pulmonary fibrosis are noted. More severely affected areas seen at the bases, left greater than right. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is stable. No acute osseous abnormalities identified.
Impression: Findings again compatible with patients known pulmonary fibrosis without definite superimposed acute process, noting that subtle change would be difficult to detect based on a portable film.
